  "title": "MANAGEMENT TRAINEE",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p>· Support ground operations across multiple F&amp;B stalls, including daily opening and closing procedures, cleanliness and compliance with hygiene standards.</p>\n<p>· Monitor and coordinate stall operators' performance, ensuring adherence to house rules, safety regulations, and service expectations.</p>\n<p>· Assist in stall allocation, onboarding and exit processes for new and existing vendors.</p>\n<p>· Work closely with operations managers and outsourced vendors to ensure smooth day-to-day operations and quick resolution of on-site issues.</p>\n<p>· Handle customer feedback and complaints in a professional and timely manner; propose solutions and escalate complex cases when necessary.</p>\n<p>· Prepare shift rosters and duty assignments to support manpower needs during peak and off-peak periods.</p>\n<p>· Track sales trends, footfall patterns and stall performance through daily reports; support the management team in analysing data to improve operations.</p>\n<p>· Support periodic audits and compliance checks, including food hygiene inspections and internal SOP reviews.</p>\n<p>· Coordinate with external contractors and suppliers (e.g., pest control, equipment servicing) to maintain operational standards.</p>\n<p>· Assist in marketing or promotional activities such as festive events, loyalty programmes, or seasonal campaigns at assigned sites.</p>\n<p>· Participate in training and development sessions to build leadership, problem-solving, and people management skills.</p>\n<p>· Perform other duties as assigned by the management.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>· Minimum Bachelor’s Degree in any discipline.</p>\n<p>· Strong willingness to learn and grow in the F&amp;B industry.</p>\n<p>· Proficient in English and Mandarin (to liaise with Mandarin-speaking colleagues).</p>\n<p>· Other languages such as Malay are a plus.</p>\n<p>· Comfortable with working 6 days a week, including weekends, public holidays, and long hours.</p>\n<p>· Good communication and interpersonal skills.</p>\n<p>· Proficient in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, PowerPoint).</p>",
